<p>I'm pretty sure there is no clean bash solution to this, but giving a shot anyway:</p>  <p>I'd like to do an html web form that does file uploads to a bash cgi script.</p>  <p>Here is the HTML I have:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;form action="../cgi-bin/upload.cgi" enctype="multipart/form-data"method="post"&gt; &lt;p&gt;Please specify a file, or a set of files:&lt;br&gt; &lt;input type="file" name="datafile"&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;input type="submit" value="Send"&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/form&gt; </code></pre>  <p>And here is the upload.cgi:</p>  <pre><code>#!/bin/bash read POSTDATA printf "Content-type: text/html\n\n" echo $POSTDATA </code></pre>  <p>So how can that script work and how can make it to upload file?</p>